    {
      "title": "Comparative and Superlative (اسم التفضيل)",
      "titleArabic": "اسم التفضيل",
      "content": [
        "The comparative/superlative form (اسم التفضيل) follows the pattern أَفْعَل. The same form serves for both comparative ('bigger than') and superlative ('biggest').",
        "The comparative is formed by placing مِنْ (than) after أفعل. The superlative is formed by making أفعل a مضاف (annexed) to the noun."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern: أَفْعَل (e.g., أَكْبَر from كَبِير)",
        "Same form for masculine, feminine, singular, and plural in comparative use",
        "Followed by مِنْ for comparison: أَكْبَرُ مِنْ (bigger than)",
        "Acts as مُضَاف for superlative: أَكْبَرُ بَيْتٍ (the biggest house)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "مُحَمَّدٌ أَكْبَرُ مِنْ عَلِيٍّ", "english": "Muhammad is bigger than Ali" },
        { "arabic": "هَذَا أَكْبَرُ بَيْتٍ", "english": "This is the biggest house" },
        { "arabic": "الْقُرْآنُ أَحْسَنُ كِتَابٍ", "english": "The Quran is the best book" }
      ]
    },
    {
